# Agent memory (this project)

Persist learnings in **`.agents/memory/`** (version-controlled). Cursor also resolves via `.cursor/agent-memory/` symlink. Skill: **`spec-agent-memory`**. Every agent role has a folder (created by `scripts/bootstrap-agent-memory.sh`).

## Start of work

1. Read `.agents/memory/_project/MEMORY.md`
2. Read `.agents/memory/_project/specs-index.md`
3. Read `.agents/memory/_project/learning-journal.md` (last 10 entries) if it exists
4. Read `.agents/memory/<your-agent-name>/MEMORY.md` (create stub if missing)

SessionStart injects a short `_project/MEMORY.md` summary (≤30 useful lines) when present — still read the full file for your role.

## End of work

Update memory with concise, durable facts:

- REQ/ARCH implementation status (update `specs-index.md`)
- Architecture and module locations discovered
- Test commands, failure modes, config/env dependencies
- Recipe used and outcome (`bug-fix`, `maintenance`, …)
- Blockers and lessons learned (especially mistakes that could recur)

## Rules

- Keep each `MEMORY.md` **under 200 lines**; use topic files for detail
- **Never store secrets** in memory files
- `.specs/` remains source of truth — memory is an index, not a substitute
- Remove or correct outdated notes

## HANDOFF

Include **Memory updated:** with paths when you changed memory files.
